document_data.mainbody:
The entry hall was a wide corridor with walls of grinning skulls and a floor of smooth stone. Enough light filtered between the exterior skull wall to dimly light this room, but the interior was dark beyond that. At the far end of the entrance corridor was a three-way intersection of hallways also lined entirely with skulls.

Deeper inside was a labyrinth in which the lower levels were somehow even more gruesome than the macabre upper levels. It contained many burial mounds{{Cite dragon/362/Grand History of the Realms: The Moonshaes}}

Over a millennium after its construction, the air within the castle was odorless and extremely dry.

